Defense lawyer Rick Hernandez requested the military judge, Colonel James Pohl, to step down due to his involvement in previous Abu Ghraib abuse cases.
Pohl expressed frustration, stating he would need to see an appearance of impropriety from two colonels and two three-star generals to recuse himself.
Hernandez argued that Private Lynndie England's guilty plea would simplify the case.
England, seen in infamous Abu Ghraib photos, admitted to following orders from her ex-boyfriend, Specialist Charles Graner.
She pleaded guilty to seven charges related to prisoner abuse, emphasizing she believed she was following orders.
